name: Pandit Ji Parantha Hut
description: Pandit Ji Parantha Hut is one place to be for all your parantha cravings. It is difficult to find a seat here as it is always crowded. They serve lip smacking paranthas at pocket friendly rates. The ambience of the place is dirty and has unclean surroundings. We ordered paneer parantha, gobhi parantha and aloo parantha. All the paranthas had generous amount of fillings. Paneer parantha was good. Gobhi parantha was a little salty. Aloo parantha was okay okay. The staff was humble but does not cater properly. They don't listen to you that easily. The service was fair enough.
author: 58c039018060197ca0b52d4c

name: Pizza Live
description:
As the name suggest pizza live they serve delicious pizzas of various varieties and also serve desserts, shakes, burger and pastas... All are good, From cost to taste everything is in their place.

There stuffs which they use are very fresh and delicious

Outlet is very small but who cares when they serve you a great things with the love

Highly recommend to all you must visit their place at once atleast it's totally worth
author: 58c039018060197ca0b52d4c

name: Food Paradise
description: This place is truly a paradise for foodies. I ordered gravy manchurian, capsicum pizza and paneer role from this outlet and each dish was just amazingly well presented as well as awesome in taste. So I recommend this place to be visited to relish some of the best food in the town.
author: 58c039018060197ca0b52d4c

name: Indian Grill Room
description: Searching for a place for team party, I came across this restaurant. The food they offer in this price range is worth for money. Entering the restaurant, you'll come across a beautifully decorated path with flowers in water pots. The outdoor seating is a must when out for dinner. As we went for lunch, we opted indoor seating which was spacious and well lit.The food served was wonderful in taste and aroma. For starters , I loved few of the dishes. The glouti kebab was mouth watering and delectable. The fish was soft and well cooked. Adding to this the chicken tikka was perfect in taste and flavor. The starters itself were quite heavy for me. So I decided to go light for the main course. My main course dishes included steam rice, boneless butter chicken, butter naan and chicken salad. The butter chicken was mellow with chicken in perfectly cooked.
author: 58c039018060197ca0b52d4c
